Proteas captain Faf du Plessis has won the toss and elected to bowl first in the Cricket World Cup opener against England at The Oval. Play starts at 11:30 (SA time). Teams England Jason Roy, Jonny Bairstow, Joe Root, Eoin Morgan (capt), Jos Buttler (wk), Ben Stokes, Moeen Ali, Chris Woakes, Adil Rashid, Jofra Archer, Liam PlunkettSouth AfricaQuinton de Kock, Hashim Amla, Aiden Markram, Faf du Plessis (captain), Rassie van der Dussen, JP Duminy, Dwaine Pretorius, Andile Phelukwayo, Kagiso Rabada, Lungi Ngidi, Imran Tahir